#### [NEW] [validation_agent.py](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/validation_agent.py)

Replaces [validator.py](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/validator.py) as the core validation module. Runs ordered validation checks that can **correct** the SQO:

| Check | On Failure | Correction |
|-------|-----------|------------|
| **Ambiguity detection** | Flag vague queries (no entities, too short, no constraints) | Infer most-likely interpretation, reduce confidence |
| **Missing constraints** | Inject defaults (scopeâ†’section-level, temporalâ†’none) | Auto-correct + log correction |
| **Entity grounding** | Verify entities exist in corpus (stub â†’ upgradeable) | Split ungrounded from grounded, warn |
| **Decomposition confidence** | Score < threshold â†’ signal re-decompose | Return `needs_redecomposition=True` |
| **Component validation** | fact_components empty / reasoning mismatch intent | Auto-fill fact from query, infer reasoning from intent |
| **SQO lock** | All checks pass â†’ freeze | Set `locked=True` |

Decision logic:
- **All checks pass** â†’ `verdict = valid`, lock SQO
- **Checks fail but correctable** â†’ apply corrections â†’ `verdict = corrected`, lock SQO
- **Confidence still below threshold after corrections** â†’ `verdict = invalid`, do NOT lock

The old [validator.py](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/validator.py) internal imports are preserved for backward compatibility ([SQOValidator](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/validator.py#34-178) â†’ `QueryValidationAgent`).

